  "caption": "I was lucky to score a table at the opening night in West End. A new neo-Nordic restaurant playing with local Queensland produce. What I experienced was thoughtful, grounded cooking from a team that cares about their craft.\n\nThe space hums with quiet passion. You can tell they know this industry is tough. Long hours. Tight margins. Big expectations. And yet, they are here for the love of it. \n\nSWIPE THROUGH FOR THE FULL REVIEW \n\nThis place has heart. You can feel it in the food and in the team. I genuinely want to support restaurants like this. If you care about produce, craft and passion on the plate, go.\n\nPictured 📸\n\t1. Kangaroo pastrami\n\t2. Sydney rock oysters\n\t3. Iced cos heart\n\t4. Buckwheat cracker, Spanish mackerel, cucumber, horseradish & Pyengana cheddar & black walnut croustade\n\t5. Malted rye & seed sourdough\n\t6. Squid noodles\n\t7. Wild venison loin\n\t8. Braised shoulder\n\t9. Buttermilk custard\n\t10. À la minute madeleines\n\t11. Review\n\t12. Vibe\n\nRatings out of 10:\nComfort: 8.5\nSoul: 9\nMastery: 9\nTaste: 9\nWould I die happy: 8.5\n\n#SasenkaLovesFood #WestEndBrisbane #BrisbaneEats #NeoNordic #QueenslandProduce OpeningNight",
